author: Josh439
body:
Good. First day of the month so had a lot of accounting shit to do. I actually had to work all day instead of browse reddit and youtube. The horror. 

On Tuesday I got my car towed to a body shop to get fixed. The tow truck was supposed to pick it up at 1pm. I went home during lunch to give my keys to him. He didn't show up until 3. 

The shop my car went to is about a 20 minute drive from my apartment. My contact at the repair place called me yesterday morning to confirm the car arrived. They said it showed up at 5...

author: StinkweedMSU
body: Robinhood exists primarily because of their lax options policies. Most brokerages require some knowledge of options with multiple levels of requirements. Robinhood just gives you the keys to the house and says "please don't burn it down." It's perfect for people that dump their entire accounts into lotto tickets.
